I cloned the site search results module and was able to add the post's featured image to the results by creating a image tag with the src being blank, then in the JS I added featuredImageUrl as a parameter to the addResult() function. Then added  `newResult.querySelector('.hs-search-results__featured').src = featuredImageUrl;` and it works but if the post doesn't have a featured image then it shows the broken image icon. I've tried adding some conditional logic in the js like so:

`
if( featuredImageUrl !== '' ) {
              newResult.querySelector('.hs-search-results__featured').src = featuredImageUrl;
            } else {
              newResult.querySelector('.hs-search-results__featured').style.display = 'none';
            }
`
but it's not working. Javascript is not my strong suit and I'm pretty new to HubSpot so not sure how to make this happen. Any advice would be greatly appreciated.

